---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const description =
  'Gardening guides and how-tos that pair with our calculators. Mulch, soil, fertilizer, watering, spacing, and more — written for real gardeners, not SEO bots.';
---

<Layout title="Blog" description={description}>
  <section class="border-b border-moss-100 bg-moss-50/60">
    <div class="container-wide py-12 sm:py-16">
      <nav class="flex text-sm text-bark-500" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <a href="/" class="hover:text-moss-800">Home</a>
        <span class="mx-2">/</span>
        <span class="text-bark-700">Blog</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="mt-4 font-display text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-bark-900 sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl">
        The HarvestMath blog
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-3 max-w-2xl text-base leading-relaxed text-bark-600 sm:text-lg">
        {description}
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container-wide py-12 sm:py-16">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-6">
      <a href="/blog/rainwater-collection-system/" class="group flex flex-col gap-4 rounded-2xl bg-white p-6 shadow-card ring-1 ring-moss-100/60 transition hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:shadow-cardHover sm:flex-row sm:items-center">
        <img
          src="/rainwater-collection-system-diagram.webp"
          alt="Labeled diagram of a rain barrel system showing the downspout, diverter, first-flush chamber, rain barrel, spigot, and overflow hose routed away from the foundation"
          width="1600"
          height="873"
          loading="lazy"
          class="w-full rounded-xl border border-moss-100 sm:w-48 sm:shrink-0"
        />
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-lg font-semibold text-bark-900 group-hover:text-moss-800">
            How to Build a Rainwater Collection System for Your Garden
          </h2>
          <p class="mt-1.5 text-sm text-bark-600">
            A step-by-step guide to setting up a rain barrel system &mdash; downspout connection, first-flush filtering, and overflow, done right.
          </p>
        </div>
      </a>

      <a href="/blog/8-mulch-mistakes-hurting-your-plants/" class="group flex flex-col gap-4 rounded-2xl bg-white p-6 shadow-card ring-1 ring-moss-100/60 transition hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:shadow-cardHover sm:flex-row sm:items-center">
        <img
          src="/correct-mulch-ring-donut-method.webp"
          alt="A young tree properly mulched with a flat, donut-shaped ring pulled back from the trunk, leaving the root flare and bark clear of mulch"
          width="1600"
          height="873"
          loading="lazy"
          class="w-full rounded-xl border border-moss-100 sm:w-48 sm:shrink-0"
        />
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-lg font-semibold text-bark-900 group-hover:text-moss-800">
            8 Mulch Mistakes That Are Secretly Hurting Your Plants
          </h2>
          <p class="mt-1.5 text-sm text-bark-600">
            The most common mulching mistakes &mdash; from volcano mulching to guessing the amount &mdash; and exactly how to avoid each one.
          </p>
        </div>
      </a>

      <a href="/blog/cool-season-vs-warm-season-grass/" class="group flex flex-col gap-4 rounded-2xl bg-white p-6 shadow-card ring-1 ring-moss-100/60 transition hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:shadow-cardHover sm:flex-row sm:items-center">
        <img
          src="/cool-season-vs-warm-season-grass-color-contrast.webp"
          alt="Illustration of two adjacent lawn patches showing the color contrast between an actively growing cool-season lawn and a dormant warm-season lawn"
          width="1200"
          height="675"
          loading="lazy"
          class="w-full rounded-xl border border-moss-100 sm:w-48 sm:shrink-0"
        />
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-lg font-semibold text-bark-900 group-hover:text-moss-800">
            Cool-Season vs. Warm-Season Grass: Which Type Do You Have?
          </h2>
          <p class="mt-1.5 text-sm text-bark-600">
            The real difference between cool-season and warm-season grass &mdash; including what to plant if you&rsquo;re in the transition zone.
          </p>
        </div>
      </a>

      <a href="/blog/topsoil-vs-garden-soil/" class="group flex flex-col gap-4 rounded-2xl bg-white p-6 shadow-card ring-1 ring-moss-100/60 transition hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:shadow-cardHover sm:flex-row sm:items-center">
        <img
          src="/topsoil-vs-garden-soil-comparison.webp"
          alt="Side-by-side comparison of plain topsoil and amended garden soil"
          width="1200"
          height="675"
          loading="lazy"
          class="w-full rounded-xl border border-moss-100 sm:w-48 sm:shrink-0"
        />
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-lg font-semibold text-bark-900 group-hover:text-moss-800">
            Topsoil vs. Garden Soil: What&rsquo;s the Difference?
          </h2>
          <p class="mt-1.5 text-sm text-bark-600">
            Topsoil and garden soil aren&rsquo;t the same thing. Here&rsquo;s the real difference, and which one your project actually needs.
          </p>
        </div>
      </a>

      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-dashed border-moss-200 bg-white p-10 text-center">
        <p class="font-display text-lg font-semibold text-bark-900">More articles landing soon.</p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-bark-600">
          We&rsquo;re publishing deep-dive guides on mulch, soil, fertilizer, and plant spacing as we ship each calculator. Check back shortly.
        </p>
        <a href="/" class="btn-secondary mt-6">&larr; Back to calculators</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
